OL,3,CVictim of murder plot GP says he will
OL,4,C'never get over the anxiety and pain'
OL,6,FMr O'Hara told the court: "I remember
OL,7,Fthat when that needle entered my arm,
OL,8,FI felt instant, excruciating pain. I
OL,9,Fhad never in my life felt anything
OL,10,Fthat painful before.
OL,12,F"I instantly thought that something
OL,13,Fhad gone wrong."
OL,15,FAfter Kwan left the home, Mr O'Hara
OL,16,Fsought medical help and spent weeks in
OL,17,Fintensive care.
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}        G9/20
