OL,3,CVictim of murder plot GP says he will
OL,4,C'never get over the anxiety and pain'
OL,6,F"In addition, I had to undertake two
OL,7,Fseparate skin grafts which involved
OL,8,Fremoving skin from my left thigh and
OL,9,Fplacing it on my injured arm."
OL,11,FHe continued: "In total I spent five
OL,12,Fweeks in hospital. I can honestly say
OL,13,Fthat there was never a day that went
OL,14,Fpast when I did not feel pain."
OL,16,FPreviously healthy Mr O'Hara said the
OL,17,Fincident "should have been the end of
OL,18,Fme" and without medical prevention he
OL,19,Fbelieves he would likely have lost his
OL,20,Farm, and his life.
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}       G11/20
