OL,3,CVictim of murder plot GP says he will
OL,4,C'never get over the anxiety and pain'
OL,6,FThe retired environmental analyst said
OL,7,Fwhile his recovery was somewhat quick,
OL,8,Fhis health took a "huge downturn" two
OL,9,Fmonths ago as a result of a diagnosed
OL,10,F"delayed stress response" which caused
OL,11,Fhim to lose one-and-a-half stone and
OL,12,Falmost all his hair.
OL,14,FHe told the court: "I have been left a
OL,15,Fshell of an individual. I suffer from
OL,16,Fextreme fatigue. Every time I get
OL,17,Fchanged I am aware of the
OL,18,Fdisfigurement of my arm which is an
OL,19,Feverlasting memory of the attack on me
OL,20,Fand this in addition has shattered my
OL,21,Fself-confidence."
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}       G12/20
